instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin lifecycle follows the typical MBSE multi‑layered abstraction hierarchy. Development begins with a Requirements layer that captures functional and performance constraints. Progressing to a Functional Architecture layer, SysML Interfaces and Block Definition Diagrams (BDDs) describe the component and connector structure, as well as the deterministic behavior via SysML state machines. A Logical Architecture layer refines the behavior into executable models, often represented by MontiArc Automata or Simulink block‑diagram models, providing a bridge between specification and implementation. The Product/Technical Architecture layer contains the physical system description and hardware‑software mapping, for instance using AADL component specifications or AADL architecture. Transitions between layers are managed through transformation rules that preserve semantics and map SysML diagrams to ADLs, allowing traceability and re‑use. Lifecycle governance is addressed implicitly by the heterogeneous stakeholder integration requirement, requiring version control, model‑library management and architecture reviews at each abstraction transition."
]

